laboratory_examinations.findings: Marked mural thickening and luminal distention of the appendix, 1.7 cm at the appendiceal tip. No periappendiceal fluid collections or free fluid/gas in abdomen or pelvis. Normal liver, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, and pancreas. A 4 cm fat containing hernia noted in the anterior abdominal wall. 3.8 cm x 2.2 cm area of fluid attenuation in left adnexa, likely a follicular cyst.
